Brief Theory of A* Algorithm
A* (A-Star) Algorithm is a searching algorithm used to find the shortest path between two nodes in a graph. It is widely used in artificial intelligence, path finding, and navigation systems.
The algorithm works by selecting the path with the minimum cost using the formula:
f(n)=g(n)+h(n)f(n)=g(n)+h(n)f(n)=g(n)+h(n)
Where:


g(n) = actual cost from start node to current node


h(n) = heuristic estimated cost from current node to goal node


f(n) = total estimated cost


A* maintains two sets:


Open Set → nodes to be explored


Closed Set → already explored nodes


The algorithm repeatedly chooses the node with the lowest f(n) value until the goal node is reached. It is efficient because it uses heuristics to reduce unnecessary searching and find the optimal path quickly.


